        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "i've wanted to count row results to build a nice helper which organizes my index-views more comfortable.\n\nso i've added ..\n{code:title=Zend\/Db\/Table.php}\n    \/**\n     * Fetches the number of row results.\n     * \n     * @return int The number of row results\n     *\/\n    public function fetchCount($where = null)\n    {\n        return (int)$this->_fetch('Count', $where);\n    }    \n{code}\n\n.. and changed .. \n\n{code:title=Zend\/Db\/Table.php - protected function _fetch}\n        \/\/ the FROM clause\n       \t$select->from($this->_name, array_keys($this->_cols));\n{code}\n\n.. to ..\n\n{code:title=Zend\/Db\/Table.php - protected function _fetch}\n        \/\/ the FROM clause\n        if ($type == 'Count') {\n        \t$select->from($this->_name, 'count(*)');\n        \t$type = 'One';\n        }\n        else\n        \t$select->from($this->_name, array_keys($this->_cols));\n{code}\n\n.. which gives me a Zend_Db_Table::fetchCount($where)-function returning the number of row results :)"
        },
